text: The Wesel citadel, German: Zitadelle Wesel, is a citadel in the town of Wesel. It was built between 1688 and 1722. Architect was Johan de Corbin. The Wesel citadel was the most important fort in Wesel. Nowadays it is used for cultural purposes. == Other websites == * Wesel citadel Category:Buildings and structures in North Rhine-Westphalia Category:Forts in Europe Category:Wesel (district) Category:18th-century buildings and structures
